          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Measurement of production cross sections of short",
                " lived nuclei by cyclic activation using a pulsed",
                " neutron source"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "J.Yamamoto",
                "J.Datemichi",
                "T.Kanaoka",
                "T.Takayama",
                "A.Takahashi",
                "K.Sumita"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2JPNOSA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ACCEL"
                ],
                "institute": "2JPNOSA"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Osaka University Accelerator used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A pulsed 14 MeV neutron source was produced",
                " by bombarding a tritium target with a D+ beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The neutron activation was made cyclic. The duration",
                " of the bursts was controlled by the D+ beam pulsing.",
                " The beam controller was interlocked with the activity",
                " counting system and was designed as to continuously",
                " change the neutron burst time and the period between",
                " bursts from 0.3ms to 54.3 ms and 0.6 ms to 108.6 ms,",
                " respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron (cyclic) activation technique was",
                " used to measure the cross-sections."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron energy spectrum of the irradiating",
                " source was analysed by TOF technique using an NE213",
                " scintillation detector as a monitor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".At present, the technique is applicable only to",
                " isotopes that emit gamma-rays."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Samples of natural lead were used, positioned at 15 cm",
                " from the neutron source and at 75 cm from the Ge",
                " detector. They were either disks of 45 mm diameter and",
                " 2 mm in thickness or hollow cylinders of dimensions,",
                " 28 mm inner diameter, 30 mm in outer diameter, 70 mm",
                " length and 1 mm thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE-IN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma activity of the irradiated samples",
                " was measured using a Ge detector. The detector",
                " was shielded against direct neutrons from the source",
                " using iron, concrete, polythene and lead."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A NE213 liquid scintillation detector was",
                " positioned at 75 cm from the Ge detector in order",
                " to monitor the neutron energy spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
